reviews.text:
Take into account that this is my local station, I have strong feelings about how this is not only the first thing I see in the morning, but for many other commuters as well...

From a lack of easily accesible bins comes litter, broken glass and once a dead rat. 

Nothing has also been done regarding smoked  cigarettes as there are no ashtrays/ cigarette disposal facilities around.

On a positive note, the member of staff who works there does try his best, but it appears that information regarding train delays/ reasons are not well informed to him.

The station desperately needs more attention given from the railway services.
